	<string name="tip_bank_1">Welcome!\n
		To use this program you have to set it up properly. Here is a little guide.\n
		First of all you need set up your \"Bank Account\" information.\n
		To do this you need:\n\n
		1. Go to "Bank Templates".\n
		2. Add new bank or choose it from the list.\n
		3. Pick up the Name, SMS sender and default currency of your account.\n
		4. Save your bank settings and make it active.\n
		5. Return to the main window.\n\n
		Do you see a list of messages from the bank?\n
		Congratulations! Your bank account is set and you are now ready to set up rules :)</string>

	<string name="tip_rules_1">
		The most important part is to set up the rules.\n
		To do this you will need:\n
		\n
		1. Go back to messages list\n
		2. One by one pick up the messages from the list which is marked with \"?\" icon.\n
		3. Choose \"Create new rule\" from the popup menu.\n
		4. Give any name to the rule.\n
		5. Pick up transaction type from the list.\n
		6. Pick all the words from the message which will never change in this type of messages. These words will be used later for extracting values. \n
		7. Press \"Next\" button and add extraction rules.\n
		\n
		TIP: You can use card number or bank account number as constant word to split messages between several accounts of the same bank.
	</string>

	<string name="tip_subrules_1">
		For each rule you need to specify a set of sub rules which can be used to extract 5 transaction parameters:\n
		\n
		1. \"Account state before transaction\"\n
		2. \"Account state after transaction\"\n
		3. \"Account state difference\"\n
		4. \"Transaction commission\" (optional)\n
		5. \"Transaction currency\" (optional)\n
		\n
		Note 1: Just 2 of first 3 parameters needed. Third parameter will be calculated automatically.\n
		\n
		Note 2: If just 1 of first 3 parameters is set program will use \"Account state\" from previous or next transaction. Sometimes it leads to wrong calculations if some previous transaction missed.\n
		\n
		Note 3: If \"Transaction currency\" is not set the default value is used from bank account settings.\n
		\n
		Note 4: If \"Transaction currency\" differs from default value set in bank account settings the exchange rate will be calculated. Sometimes it leads to wrong calculations if some previous transaction missed.\n
		\n
		Note 5: If \"Transaction commission\" is not set the default value is zero.\n
		\n
		Note 6: To delete the rule just uncheck the checkbox.
	</string>

